some of the basic features of java are as follows:- 
1.Simple and Familiar: Java is simple because its coding style is very clean and easy to understand.it is familiar because it has a base of familiar languages like C and C++ and contains many features of these languages.
2.Compiled and Interpreted    
3.Platform Independent: java achieves platform independence by using the concept of the BYTE code.
4.Portable
5.Architectural Neutral
6.Object-Oriented
7.Robust: Java is robust as it is capable of handling run-time errors, supports automatic garbage collection and exception handling, and avoids explicit pointer concept.
8.Secure
9.Distributed: Java is distributed because it encourages users to create distributed applications.
10.Multi-threaded and Interactive
11.High Performance
12.Dynamic and Extensible                
